RACE.RACE_TEXT: Downs At Albuquerque H. ALBUQUERQUE RACE 5 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 108. Stakes Purse 200000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER. No nomination fee. By subscription of $1,500.00 to pass the entry box and an additional $2,000.00 to start with $200,000 guaranteed of which $108,000 to the owner of the winner, $40,000 to second, $20,000 to third, $10,000 t o fourth, $6,000 to fifth and $4,000 for placing sixth and $3,000 for placing seventh through tenth. If fewer than ten horses start, the purse money not distributed will revert to the winning owner. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usualt ime of closing. Field limited to Twelve (12) starters. Horses not drawing a starting position in the gate will receive a refund of the entry fee. HIGH WEIGHTS PREFERRED. Nominations close Wednesday October 11, 2023 at 2:00 pm. RACE WILL BE LASIX FREE. ( A Trophy will be presented to the winning Owner).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BYE BYE BOBBY was settled early towards the inside, made a inside bid by the three eighths marker to vie for command, then came off the inside leaving the turn while leading, then turned back a bid from TRUTH SEEKER despite being on the left lead and edged clear to prove best, driving. PRESIDENTIAL was reserved early on the inside, saved ground on the turn while advancing, then finished willingly to gain the place award late. TRUTH SEEKER was off slowly, then settled back early, shifted out and made a five wide move by the quarter pole, continued that move to loom boldly in the lane but hung late. MINE THAT STAR was five wide into the first turn, chased the pace four to five wide, made a four wide bid on the turn but flattened out, bested rest. ARHAM was four wide into the first turn, stalked the pace three wide and made a three wide bid on the turn but weakened. BIGFOOT CITY was off a step slow, set the pace while racing removed from the rail, headed by the three eighths marker and gave way. THIS RACE IS HAND TIMED.
